    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-10T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-10T13:00:00-05:00" n="126"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d126">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/3291</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DG1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Droppers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-10T20:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 10, 1917, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received February 11, 7.30 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>251. Replying to your circular telegram 4th [<hi rend="italic">3d</hi>].<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d126fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_108">p. 108</ref>.</note>
                    Greek Government shares President’s solicitude for world peace and safety of <pb
                        facs="0299" n="127" xml:id="pg_127"/> seas. Has formulated “express
                    reserves” to German Government in regard to latter’s blockade plans, but in view
                    of peculiar situation of Greece at this time can not take united action with
                    American Government. Text of reply to be forwarded by mail.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d126fn1">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Droppers</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
